pull_request.title: Add MLX support and refactor model architecture
pull_request.body:
This PR introduces support for the MLX framework and refactors the model architecture to accommodate both PyTorch and MLX implementations. The changes include:

- Added new `mlx` directory with MLX-specific model and training implementations
- Refactored the existing PyTorch model into `nue/model/torch.py`
- Created a new base `GPTConfig` class in `nue/model/base.py` for shared configuration
- Updated the CLI to support choosing between PyTorch and MLX frameworks
- Added new GitHub Actions workflow for MLX-specific CI on macOS
- Updated dependencies to include MLX as an optional extra

commits.message:
tvheadend: update to 2024-11-12, new options, patch for bug #26422

Changes:
- update to git master 2024-11-12 (dev stalled since then)
- patch for OpenWrt bug #26422 / tvheadend bug #1786
- Options removed:
  - imagecache = tvheadend doesn't support disabling it anymore
- Options added:
  - detailed (but slow) memory utilization reporting
  - Timeshift (default on)
  - tsfile (currently bugged in tvheadend, commented out / always on)
  - HDHomeRun server emulation (default on)
  - Digital Devices DVB CI descrambling cards (default off)
- RegEx options cleaned up, PCRE2 is the new default.
- Some help text improved

Signed-off-by: Marius Dinu <m95d+git@psihoexpert.ro>

after a sysupgrade, the reinstalled package config files overwrite what
is on disk rather than being placed as conf-opkg. Defining these config
files will preserve them appropriately.
